Package com.tiyb.tev.xml.helper

Class PrettyPrintHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.tiyb.tev.xml.helper.PrettyPrintHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    InvocationHandler
    public class PrettyPrintHandler
extends Object
implements InvocationHandler
    Helper class used to wrap the StAX classes, for creating a more readable version of the XML output by inserting newlines and indentation into the output.
    Author:
    tiyb

    • Method Detail

      • invoke

        public Object invoke​(Object proxy,
                     Method method,
                     Object[] args)
              throws Throwable
        Method which is allowing this code to wrap the underlying XML stream writer method. Catches each call to writeStartElement() or writeEmptyElement() or writeEndElement() to insert newlines and spaces as needed, before invoking the underlying object's method. (Underlying method is always invoked, regardless of whether pretty printing was added or not.)
        Specified by:
        invoke in interface InvocationHandler
        Parameters:
        proxy - The object being proxied
        method - The method of the oject being proxied
        args - The arguments being passed to that method
        Returns:
        Always returns null
        Throws:
        Throwable

      • repeat

        private String repeat​(int depthToRepeat,
                      String indentChar)
        Helper function to repeat a given string the given number of times. For performance reasons, streams are used rather than string concatenation.
        Parameters:
        depthToRepeat - The number of times to repeat the string.
        indentChar - The string to be repeated
        Returns:
        The generated string
